    {
      "Case Number": "PCN02283045",
      "Case Title": "CONSERVATORSHIP OF DONALD F. JOHNSON",
      "Court Date": "2004-09-14 10:30 AM",
      "Examiner": "JOCELYN ROQUE",
      "Calendar Matter": "To Produce Documents Requested In Deposition Notices And To Compel Answers To Deposition Questions And Points Authoritues In Support Of Motion.",
      "Rulings": "Petitioner's Motion To Produce Documents Requested In Deposition Notices and To Compel Answers To Deposition Questions is granted in part and denied in part. The motion is granted as to the Document Requests Nos. 5 and 6 as to Casteel and Document Requests Nos. 3 and 4 as to Patterson, limited to the period 10 years prior to the date of the allegations of this complaint. The requests for documents as to both defendant is not overly broad, and their right to financial privacy is outweighed by the relevance of the documents sought by the requests. The names of other persons who are not defendants in this action and the amounts invested in any transaction may be redacted. The motion is granted in part, denied in part, and moot in part as to the deposition questions. Questions about tax documents have been withdrawn. Questions about the names of limited partners who are not named defendants are not relevant and invade the non-defendants' right to privacy as it relates to their identity. The court finds that questions about the amount of any investments in the transactions are not relevant. All requests for sanctions are denied. (612/EHEWLETT)",
      "Judge": "Jocelyn Roque"
    },
